    }
  ],
  "inter_chunk_silence_ms": 650,
  "chunks": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "text": "OpenAI just opened a new front. Not a chat product.",
      "checksum": "sha256:51f35f3b015a4f48849b91b510936ed61cb4c2042823c60f3bc1ecf1d0dde73a",
      "wav": "chunk-00.wav",
      "duration": 3.1579138321995464,
      "word_count": 10,
      "words_offset": 0
    },
    {
      "index": 1,
      "text": "Not an image model. A security program. They call it Daybreak.",
      "checksum": "sha256:c398f0e421bf26401fc64860fa59d206df916f8bdcc009b9cb85880018dea7b9",
      "wav": "chunk-01.wav",
      "duration": 3.3436734693877552,
      "word_count": 11,
      "words_offset": 10
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "text": "Frontier intelligence pointed at cyber defense, not at users.",
      "checksum": "sha256:8fd7c9f5bf62911281338fecf038e6f2f76e4fc09ca5eceaabac330147278b64",
      "wav": "chunk-02.wav",
      "duration": 3.5294331065759637,
      "word_count": 9,
      "words_offset": 21
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "text": "But here's the twist. Anthropic shipped Claude Mythos a month ago for the same job.",
      "checksum": "sha256:df8a44ff484eab63bb8c80601b00ac3e8758b8d6186350079a4000937dfa01cc",
      "wav": "chunk-03.wav",
      "duration": 4.31891156462585,
      "word_count": 15,
      "words_offset": 30
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "text": "Same partners. Cisco. CrowdStrike. So is Daybreak just OpenAI's answer?",
      "checksum": "sha256:1778d10d87ea083e421cf77694c708bfd5e4c7b12c3189bf1a81aaf0beff52bc",
      "wav": "chunk-04.wav",
      "duration": 5.201269841269841,
      "word_count": 10,
      "words_offset": 45
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "text": "Or is this actually different? Daybreak fuses OpenAI's most capable models with Codex.",
      "checksum": "sha256:f9a93539343cd67a539891d0a3274ce5c5c844a88e05415574e50bb102c9e9fd",
      "wav": "chunk-05.wav",
      "duration": 5.154829931972789,
      "word_count": 13,
      "words_offset": 55
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "text": "The whole stack runs on 3 GPT five point five variants.",
      "checksum": "sha256:44a22e27e3f03f17dd00f19672005f913189e33beed0cd7ae9d0a8fe97c1c156",
      "wav": "chunk-06.wav",
      "duration": 3.3901133786848074,
      "word_count": 11,
      "words_offset": 68
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "text": "The first one is standard GPT five point five, for everyday secure development inside your own repos.",
      "checksum": "sha256:c84bf6be300ee99013d0c908fdf1aaeb0fa33de9acda9bcad5f56f1c369ff41d",
      "wav": "chunk-07.wav",
      "duration": 5.758548752834467,
      "word_count": 17,
      "words_offset": 79
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "text": "The second is GPT five point five with Trusted Access for Cyber.",
      "checksum": "sha256:4349d14a6c148fd79e65769597ca039a1de14fdbc416bc9a0fd095a353418955",
      "wav": "chunk-08.wav",
      "duration": 4.272471655328798,
      "word_count": 12,
      "words_offset": 96
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "text": "That one is verified defensive work, inside authorized environments only.",
      "checksum": "sha256:639a51f621c3c97f8d87ded6de921ee8137993a250d2e50b49b5c86821d17a77",
      "wav": "chunk-09.wav",
      "duration": 4.133151927437642,
      "word_count": 10,
      "words_offset": 108
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "text": "The third is GPT five point five Cyber. A permissive model that opens the door for red teaming and controlled penetration testing.",
      "checksum": "sha256:ce16ed3b19ef953aaa15a064e62e78cb6d356b86b9b49b90b0c589509d540c4e",
      "wav": "chunk-10.wav",
      "duration": 7.7090249433106575,
      "word_count": 22,
      "words_offset": 118
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "text": "3 tiers. 1 mission. Together they cover the full defender toolset.",
      "checksum": "sha256:0a9c18adf33167f81b6cc429f5552a972818d634a1861ed12396fec810bc5e99",
      "wav": "chunk-11.wav",
      "duration": 4.458231292517007,
      "word_count": 11,
      "words_offset": 140
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "text": "Secure code review. Threat modeling. Patch validation.",
      "checksum": "sha256:04319bcb5879808e060562538d7eb1b0c209092866aeab81e29d5ccf3327a6ba",
      "wav": "chunk-12.wav",
      "duration": 3.2043537414965986,
      "word_count": 7,
      "words_offset": 151
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "text": "Dependency risk analysis. Detection. And remediation guidance.",
      "checksum": "sha256:5198ab76583d4f1d804292297f7471bb0890f121a394cd0728deeb38a601f1e8",
      "wav": "chunk-13.wav",
      "duration": 3.900952380952381,
      "word_count": 7,
      "words_offset": 158
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "text": "All of it sits inside the everyday development loop, not behind a separate dashboard.",
      "checksum": "sha256:6571f7ab9f56330d67db00d8464e8900eb7206ef1696c91d1698372bff320c23",
      "wav": "chunk-14.wav",
      "duration": 4.690430839002268,
      "word_count": 14,
      "words_offset": 165
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "text": "Codex Security is at the center. The day a vulnerability is found, the patch is already written.",
      "checksum": "sha256:ed9a647131e13a16b5c317e9d1f7203882cbfb6da4eb1cec5268928caf0670a3",
      "wav": "chunk-15.wav",
      "duration": 5.2477097505668935,
      "word_count": 17,
      "words_offset": 179
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "text": "The launch partners are not small. 8 names every defender already knows.",
      "checksum": "sha256:7506f4a6d17c786030719be79c2a8c77d5c60004ad3cbea5f252e5f645afb94b",
      "wav": "chunk-16.wav",
      "duration": 4.133151927437642,
      "word_count": 12,
      "words_offset": 196
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "text": "Akamai. Cisco. Cloudflare. CrowdStrike. Fortinet.",
      "checksum": "sha256:c258f29a327a52dafdeda7fabfe3f9ca4971adbeaaac44d51aaef9ddae3e25d6",
      "wav": "chunk-17.wav",
      "duration": 3.111473922902494,
      "word_count": 5,
      "words_offset": 208
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "text": "Oracle. Palo Alto Networks. Zscaler. All 8 integrating Daybreak under the Trusted Access for Cyber program.",
      "checksum": "sha256:a6bd1e2b09e2f0e87694919b71108b3ada281c61e57b8245f32974a02ca4a71d",
      "wav": "chunk-18.wav",
      "duration": 7.244625850340136,
      "word_count": 16,
      "words_offset": 213
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "text": "The launch tweet hit 2.4 million views in 10 hours.",
      "checksum": "sha256:465c3963734d026b9d2c858ac34d4059818c075ff3d994893a573e3248439a87",
      "wav": "chunk-19.wav",
      "duration": 3.111473922902494,
      "word_count": 10,
      "words_offset": 229
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "text": "So here's the real difference. Mythos hunts zero-days.",
      "checksum": "sha256:98f92cea364b5f8d6ae61f7dc1aaa40fab744043949f4bca3a55bda56b1227c9",
      "wav": "chunk-20.wav",
      "duration": 3.2043537414965986,
      "word_count": 8,
      "words_offset": 239
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "text": "Daybreak ships the patch. Same battlefield.",
      "checksum": "sha256:b3211c32112b7c27af2b71bde502237dbcc4e13e1a0693c73e7e9bc7a870857d",
      "wav": "chunk-21.wav",
      "duration": 2.36843537414966,
      "word_count": 6,
      "words_offset": 247
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "text": "Opposite ends. This is the shift. Defenders that used to be outpaced by attackers now move at the same speed. Daybreak is rolling out broader access with industry and government partners in the coming weeks.",
      "checksum": "sha256:48a3e7d22868c0726c0d9704ec07af4c6df26d0a21c2590c2baa84403398c784",
      "wav": "chunk-22.wav",
      "duration": 12.863854875283447,
      "word_count": 35,
      "words_offset": 253
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "text": "Want a vulnerability scan today? OpenAI says request one.",
      "checksum": "sha256:e01cabbe08f3fc80952713924453040dabdabea0c79533e13842b6b93273a2e5",
      "wav": "chunk-23.wav",
      "duration": 3.3436734693877552,
      "word_count": 9,
      "words_offset": 288
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "text": "The window between disclosure and patch just collapsed. Software stops being secure the day it ships.",
      "checksum": "sha256:fc97034fcf6783c4e6592a50df4ee3d37b62a4f126b6645e0eae6f514584d25b",
      "wav": "chunk-24.wav",
      "duration": 5.61922902494331,
      "word_count": 16,
      "words_offset": 297
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "text": "Now it gets continuously secured. If you want to learn more about AI, check out the dynamous dot AI community.",
      "checksum": "sha256:c6c199af4e2d80d2bfa3f943ed208bc27f62ca282dd8925a578490afa331f336",
      "wav": "chunk-25.wav",
      "duration": 6.03718820861678,
      "word_count": 20,
      "words_offset": 313
    }
  ]
}